label: dietary chemical component
definition: A material entity that is ingested and contributes to survival, growth and development

label: dry plant matter
definition: Material which remains after the removal of water from plant matter.

label: available carbohydrate
definition: Carbohydrates that are absorbed in the small intestine and provide carbohydrate for metabolism in monogastric animals.

label: free sugar
definition: Available carbohydrate in monosaccharide and disaccharide form

label: dietary fibre
definition: A carbohydrate that resists enzymatic digestion in the digestive systems of humans and other monogastric species.

label: soluble dietary fibre
definition: Dietary fibre which dissolves in water and is primarily fermented in the colon of monogastric animals by gut bacteria

label: resistant starch
definition: A portion of starch that cannot be digested by amylases in the small intestine

label: insoluble dietary fibre
definition: Dietary fibre which does not dissolve in water and is inert to digestive enzymes in the upper gastrointestinal tract of monogastric animals.

label: seed storage protein
definition: A protein that accumulates in developing seeds or grains.

label: mineral nutrient
definition: A mineral that is an inorganic nutrient which must be ingested and absorbed in adequate amounts to satisfy a wide range of essential metabolic and/or structural functions in the human body

label: macro element
